Hey everyone! This is the original cover art for the Devil Spy book! The cover will be digitally inked and colored for print, but this original had inked and colored art is available as a reward through the Devil Spy Book Kickstarter! The art is on 11"x17" bristol board paper and is drawn and colored with Copic ink and markers. It's all one piece, the shadow line in the center is from my scanner. :)

The Devil Spy Book Kickstarter has just one week left to reach goal! I know we still have a long way to go to get funded, but I have my fingers crossed that we can get there in the next week! I really want to make these books for you all! If you want to help, here's what you can do:

SHARE the link to the Kickstarter campaign everywhere you can! It doesn't cost you anything to reblog/retweet my posts on Tumblr and Twitter, my username is Jaymzeecat on most social media. Share them on Facebook, you can get them directly from the Devil Spy Facebook page. Or make new posts of your own. If you know of anywhere else I should try posting, please let me know! If you're a fan of Devil Spy and you believe in this series, please tell people about it! If you have friends you think would like it, please spread the word! Sharing is IMMENSELY helpful!

DRAW some fan art for Devil Spy! Fan art helps me show people that there is an interest in the comic! And it gives me something to post other than my monotonous Kickstarter posts! 

PLEDGE to the Kickstarter! Even if you don't want to buy the book right now, you can pledge just $1-$5. If everyone who subscribed to Devil Spy pledged just the cost of a cup of coffee, the book would already be funded! If you're planning to just buy the book later, please note that there wont be a book if the Kickstarter doesn't meet the funding goal in the next seven days. So please help me get the word out!

These are all things that would be incredibly helpful! Thank you so much! And thank you to everyone who's backed the book and shared the link to the Kickstarter so far! I can't wait to make these books for you and I'm praying for a miracle that we are able to get there with only a week to do it!

I hope you are all having a rad day!

Link to the Kickstarter: https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/jaymzbernard/devil-spy-book-one

campaign_name: Niel Nasset Needs Your Help to Produce a New LP Record
message: We got 11 days left. If we don't get enough funding, we get nothing. Here's the deal. Someone was asking "Why so much?" We're trying to do several things. 10-12 song album (narrowed down from a large batch that we haven't even figured out yet). For just me to track the song you're looking at $500 a song. Just me. To make the songs beautiful, we add my friends. $50-200 more a song for each musician. No mastering, no nothing. Just a raw ass song. Then, we send said songs to mastering. Another $100-200 a song. Then there's actually printing the cd let alone a vinyl. Then there's merch. Tee's, tanks, koozies, stickers....Smallest batch $500. My boys at coloredlion.com haven't even been paid for the video (out of their good graces). This is the only way for independent songwriters to get their stuff out there. I've been out of the game for a few but I'm back and ready for you to hear what I've been writing. So if you want to help the little guys, please listen and share and DONATE (if you can) https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/nielnasset/niel-nasset-needs-your-help-to-produce-a-new-lp-re?ref=nav_search

One of the subjects in our film became an online villain as a result of the Internet witch hunt to find Elisa's 'killer.' Now a father, he STILL gets death threats. In the midst of this turbulence--which included YouTube suspending his band's account--he had a dream in which #ElisaLam came to him and said she left a diary at the Los Angeles train station.

The more down the rabbit hole I went with this case, the more I found myself navigating stories like the one above - now there's just a backlog of tales that need to be told. So many angles, different ways people have found their lives inextricably linked to Elisa's. Some people suffering from depression visit her blog just to read about her struggle, which she detailed so meticulously.

An unlikely community has arisen from the ashes of this tragic story. Can you chip in to help us tell this incredible story?

General Cheng & The Ming Dynasty

The Ming Dynasty is the ruling dynasty of China that followed the fall of the Yuan Dynasty. With its capital in Beijing, the Ming Dynasty boasts one of the most organized governments and socially stable economies. An army of over a million troops makes the Ming Dynasty the most formidable force in the world. General Cheng, an accomplished voyager and military tactician, was sent by the Emperor to Atala to investigate the presence of ancient and very powerful relics called the Dragon Stones. Upon his failure to subdue the Atalians, Cheng called for massive reinforcements from Ming, but not before setting his eyes on the Empire of Azzaz after an apparent interference on their behalf.

campaign_name: Cat Caf’© Studio: India's First Cat Caf’©
message:
Gabriel: "sis.. Stop doing that, people are watching." 
Jill: "I'm trying to wake mama up, remember how we used to suckle as kittens and she would wake up and start loving us.." 
Gabriel: "Yes, as kittens! I'm a grown up now, can't talk for you though. Damn, I regret suggesting we ask her about the funding thingy." 
Jill: "Well, we are running out of time, only 5 hours to go now. What is going to happen to Cat Caf’© Studio when their Kickstarter campaign fails!? No money, no more cats. Don't you get it?" 
Gabriel: "From what I know abt hoomans, they freak out if they don't know what to do. I don't see anyone freaking out here, do you?" 
Jill: "How would we? We are not at the Cat Caf’© anymore thanks to the hoomans who got us adopted in this lovely home. Aren't you worried at all? What about all the lovely ppl who would come every day just to meet and spend time with cats who would be neglected on the streets otherwise. What will happen to them, where will they go now? You see.. "
Gabriel: "Okay now I'm starting to get a bit worried. Wait, what does Mama like? Can we open a wet food pouch and.." 
Jill: "Say no more."

As we roll into mental health week (October 8th -15th) for 2016, I would like to touch on a key point that I have found to be a common comment and focus, from the first twenty interviews in "Masked; Follow The Rabbit",

Mental illness takes no time off, no exemptions, no mercy and it can happen to anyone, It is important - year round, not just this week, that we are supportive, understanding and aware of the people around us who may need an extra support line every now and again to keep their heads above water.

For those of you who are interested in helping to raise awareness and give 250 people a platform and voice to share their journey, story and experience of living with mental health issues in Australia, I urge you to please take a moment to open my Kick-starter link. 

There are several options for donating, via a photo-shoot, booking an interview, sponsoring an interview & photo-shoot for someone less financially fortunate, purchasing merch or the "Masked; Follow The Rabbit" first edition book - (prices will rise for following editions as these are a special kick-starter price). All of the funds raised will go directly towards production and printing 50 books. 

5 books (10% of the total first editions) will be donated to willing and participating Melbourne and outer suburb Head space branches, for youths to flick through and hopefully benefit from knowing other people feel how they might be feeling, have faced similar struggles, that It can get better, You are not alone.

Please take a moment, have a read and a look, more updates, sneak peeks and videos will be uploaded to the official kick-starter funding page throughout this week and coming months in our last big stretch to reach our goal.

Thank you to everyone who has expressed interest, booked in, donated, shared their story or told their loved ones.

We still need 230 willing participants, sessions are only $10 - which can also be donated. For those of you wanting to contribute but not participate, donations help us to help someone else less fortunate to share their journey too.

Let's do this together, we are on the home stretch of the funding and the beginning of the sessions, I encourage you all to be brave and step forward. All sessions remain anonymous and "MASKED".

<3

message:
RIYRIA #GraphicNovel 's #Kickstarter has been live for FIVE HOURS and we are killing it!!! Dabel Brothers Publishing brings to life the story from #TheDeathOfDulgath by Michael J. Sullivan!! http://buff.ly/2cTW66o

WANT TO KNOW ABOU THIS PROJECT
Best-selling author Michael J. Sullivan teams up with Dabel Brothers Publishing, artists Max Raynor and Michael Bartolo, comic adaptation writer Derek Ruiz and letterer and production designer Dave Lanphear to bring Riyria to the graphic novel format for the first time. Sullivan's fantasy novel, The Death of Dulgath was Kickstarter's most successful fantasy novel project, and now it will be adapted into a two volume graphic novel series. The story will be lovingly interpreted in the visual form and supported by bonus material that is sure to excite any fan of fantasy who longs for that inside look into the making of the graphic novel.

Without such a generous fan base and the rampant support for the original novel of The Death Of Dulgath, the graphic novel would not be possible. We need your help again to propel Michael's work towards even further success. More than any other fantasy author today, Sullivan's extensive imagination merits a visual narrative.

<3 Gladys #XOXOtheNerdGirl #NerdGirlOfficial #NerdGirlArmy #TeamDabel #IStreetTeam

campaign_name: Aaron Lee Martin - New Album "Learned Behavior"
message:
I woke up from a sobering dream around 5:30 this morning. Historically, I'm not the type that remembers my dreams, but this one felt strangely poignant to me. I don't remember much of it, but here's what I recall:

Someone (a face I didn't recognize) was crouched on the ground, wounded, dying in front of me. The figure started out as an animal (a deer, a horse maybe?), but then began to morph into the form and presence of a woman. I don't think it was my wife, because I couldn't nail down a distinct relationship with the creature, but I know in this dream, I loved her deeply. 

And it wasn't just romantic love that I felt for her. This love had movement. It transitioned from romantic love, to the love I feel for a friend, to the love I felt for my mother, to the love I feel for a stranger, to maybe even the love I feel for God. 

I was overcome with grief and sorrow and panic at the thought of losing her. I frantically began to weep and shout "No, you can't leave yet! I haven't had enough time with you! I don't know how to live this life without you! Please stay!"
And she looked me in the eyes, with all grace, compassion, empathy and transcendence and very calmly spoke,

"Love is not about you. It is only the love you give and not the love you receive that matters."

The moment she spoke those words, I became unattached to the thought of her dying or the fact that I would never see her again and felt a wave of overwhelming peace. I no longer felt like I would be empty or lost without her and I began to feel like I was a part of the greater whole.

I abruptly awoke with tears in my eyes and a sense that I'd collected another puzzle piece to assist with this whole "life" thing and cuddled my hungry, unusually affectionate kitties, before getting up to feed them.

Now, whether that dream has meaning or is just the result of watching too many Disney movies in my lifetime, I don't know...

But it does feel like a slightly more interesting prelude, to let you know that there are still 7 days left on my Kickstarter. 
Thanks to YOU, the project has been fully funded! 
I'm now working on a stretch goal of $7,000 (currently at $6,600) in order to press some vinyl of my upcoming album Learned Behavior.
But I mostly just wanted to let you know, that there is still time to be a part of the pre-sale and grab some of the exclusive rewards that you'll only find on my Kickstarter.
So check it out, share it if you feel inclined and know that you guys have made me feel so loved and supported throughout this process! 
Thank you!
<3

One of our backers, Matt backed our game to get his friends dog a tag. Zack and his partner Stef rescued this little guy in Ecuador. Here is his story.

During our trip to Ecuador, a man drew us a map on a napkin to navigate the way after the main road was washed out in a storm. Along the way, a dirty, shaggy, matted white dog with creepy white eyes started following us. Although we'd been wary of many dogs here, we gave this one a chance. He seemed keen on adventure apparently!

What followed was an epic day. This alternate road was a journey up and down and up canyons mostly covered in sand too deep to bike on. Since we were going on what should have been a short ride, we didn't have much food for the poor guy for a while. 

We finally made it to the famous Quilotoa Crater where we bought him a sausage he ate in one bite. The next day, we weren't surprised to find our new friend ready to hike with us. This time, we planned ahead and packed food for three.

The following day was time to say goodbye since we were going to take the highway for a bit. Our friend stayed in our mind for the rest of the journey. 
Weeks later, I rented a car and drove four hours back to Quilotoa. It was a long shot but I had to see if he was there. Fate had it that I found that same little white dog with light blue eyes in a village nearby.

He jumped in the car, off to a groomer. The result was the cutest little thing I have ever seen. Soon we were on our way to Victoria, Canada, the new home he has loved since then!

After testing it was determined that Quito is 40% Poodle.
Thank you for your support, Maria Rodriguez!

campaign_name: The Mastery Journal by John Lee Dumas
message:
1 challenge that will change your life, and allow you to choose freedom. 

For 12 months, I studied every aspect of productivity, discipline and focus.

I learned a lot, and today I'll share my #1 takeaway.

The Pomodoro Technique.

The Pomodoro Technique is a time management method developed by Francesco Cirillo in the late 1980s. The technique uses a timer to break down work into intervals, traditionally 25 minutes in length, separated by short breaks.

I resisted the timer and the intervals for a long time, but FINALLY tested them...

When I actually pressed the timer and started to work, #gamechanger.

Your mind shifts to a different place as soon as you press go, and the next 25 minutes will be the most productive of your day, PERIOD.

Personally, I found 25 minutes were too short for my mindset, and through trial and error I found 42 minutes of FOCUS time, followed by 18 minutes of REFRESH time was my sweet spot.

It's important to note the REFRESH time is as critical as the FOCUS time. Don't skimp on either. I use my refresh time to meditate, journal, etc...

When I started using The Pomodoro Technique daily, I realized it was going to be a KEY component of The Mastery Journal.

Within The Mastery Journal, there are FOUR daily sessions where The Pomodoro Technique is utilized.

You'll get more done in these four sessions than you used to get done all week.

campaign_name: Inner Compass cards: a new way of self-reflection
message:
How to use the Inner Compass deck?
Some people like to use the deck every morning for a specific card to guide their day. Others might pick a card periodically, to shed light on an urgent issue or a question they might have.Î¾
Sometimes you just want to know if you are heading the right way. At other times, you might need help to find a way out. Maybe you just want to leave it open, letting any associations come freely upon drawing a card.
Whatever the motive, after shuffling the deck with your focus and intention, just blindly pick one or more cards. Your intuition will guide you to find new patterns of meaning. It is impossible to choose the wrong card: the right one will always present itself!

Come join us for the monthly Anime PDX/Newcon PDX planning meeting of 2017.  

We will officially opening up submissions this day for those that wish to staff.  If you are interested in being part of the team (especially those wishing to join as Coordinators or Managers) this is a great meeting.  We prefer to hire those who can make at least one meeting prior to the convention.

You can staff one or both events (though we generally prefer our managerial staff to work both events).  

We will cover our planning for Anime PDX and touch on Newcon PDX.  Annouce updates and talk about what we have in store.

message: The space in which the song Blizzard takes place is a cozy cabin in the woods. Everything is covered with snow, the kind that hasnŠ—Èt yet been disturbed by footprints. The moon is full, with seemingly frozen beams of light delicately shooting through the trees. It illuminates the faint spectral glimmers of the white fluff. In this moment there is not cold, there is not suffering, there is not otherness. campaign_name: The Whatamagump (a hand-crafted story picture book)
message: The clay sculpture of Mr. Gump gets cut from his #silicone mold! Separate molds were made for each of his arms, legs, wings and teeth. After putting the two sides back together, we pour liquid resin inside and when it cures, we've got a Whatamagump ready for assembly and painting! This process allows us to make duplicates in several hours instead of several days days. However,  because his gestures and expressions will differ from page to page in the book, each copy of him will require additional modification.\n\n#whatisawhatamagump #thewhatamagump #siliconemold #artdoll #handmade #tyronewells #brokenesglestudio #portlandartist #portland #sculpture #sculptor #sculpting #resincasting

campaign_name: Mensch - A Short Film About PTSD
message: Get to know our Lead Actor Kyle Krogen, who will be portraying James.\n\nKyle is originally from a small town in southwestern Wisconsin. Ever since he was young he had always found solace in cinema. It was two hours where the rest of the world seemed to disappear and where Kyle found inspiration and courage from these stories and their characters. Many years later, he found himself being pushed towards creating, and being these characters himself. Since then, Kyle has studied his craft in both Chicago and Los Angeles, and has worked on projects across the United States.

campaign_name: The Whatamagump (a hand-crafted story picture book)
message: One of the bigger challenges with building Julie's bedroom was making it look like a 'lived in' kid's bedroom. I child's room is messy and cluttered and has lots of trinkets and stuff scattered about. In the case of this set, filling that space with individually handmade 'clutter' was tedious and time consuming and took more time than building the walls and furniture. It seemed that no matter how much was built, we kept needing to make more! \n#dinosaurs #tinythings #thewhatamagump #whatisawhatamagump #sculpture #tinysculptures #supersculpey #handmadeart #clutter #childrensbook #kidsbook #lowbrowart #quarter #scalemodel #scale #miniature #portland #portlandartist #brokeneaglestudio #tyronewells
